# DS-0002: "Specify at least 1 USER command in Dockerfile with non-root user".
# Accepted risk, deliberately: CraftDock's entire purpose is to control the
# Minecraft container through /var/run/docker.sock (root-equivalent by design)
# and to read/write world files the game server creates with mixed ownership.
# Running as a non-root user would break the docker.sock connection on most
# hosts (socket is root:docker with a host-specific GID) without reducing the
# real attack surface — the socket mount, not the container user, is the power.
# Access is gated by the panel's bcrypt-authenticated session on every route.
DS-0002
